Document: OpenXRActionSet
Path: godot/classes/class_openxractionset.rst
Summary: Core methods for managing actions in an OpenXR action set, including adding, removing, and querying actions.

- Method: add_action(action: OpenXRAction) → void. Adds the specified action to the action set.
- Method: get_action_count() → int. Returns the number of actions in the action set. Constant method.
- Method: remove_action(action: OpenXRAction) → void. Removes the specified action from the action set.
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRActionSet
Path: godot/classes/class_openxractionset.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for managing action sets in OpenXR.

Property: actions (Array): Collection of actions for this action set. Default: empty array. Set via set_actions(value: Array), get via get_actions().

Property: localized_name (String): The localized name of this action set. Default: empty string. Set via set_localized_name(value: String), get via get_localized_name().

Property: priority (int): The priority for this action set. Default: 0. Set via set_priority(value: int), get via get_priority(). Higher values indicate higher priority when resolving input conflicts.
---CHUNK---
Document: OpenXRActionSet
Path: godot/classes/class_openxractionset.rst
Summary: Methods for adding, removing, and querying actions in an OpenXR action set.

Method: add_action(action: OpenXRAction) → void. Add an action to this action set.

Method: get_action_count() → int. Retrieve the number of actions in our action set.

Method: remove_action(action: OpenXRAction) → void. Remove an action from this action set.